<h2>Fees for Certificates of Free Sale and Sanitation and/or Certificates of Origin and Sanitation</h2>
<ol>
	<li><strong><em>Original certificate.</em></strong> All applicants for certificates shall pay a nonrefundable fee based on the number of products to be listed on the certificate. Certificates shall not be reproduced or transferred from one person to another or from one establishment to another. </li>
	<li><strong><em>Additional certificates</em>.</strong> Each additional identical original certificate is about 10% of the base fee. </li>
	<li><strong> <em>The fee schedule.</em></strong>
		<ul>
			<li>$50 for 1 - 50 products per original certificate; $5 for each additional identical certificate</li>
			<li>$60 for 51 - 200 products per original certificate; $6 for each additional identical certificate </li>
			<li>$75 for 201 - 500 products per original certificate; $8 for each additional identical certificate </li>
			<li>$100 for 501 - 1000 products per original certificate; $10 for each additional identical certificate </li>
		</ul>
	</li>		
	<li><strong><em>Cosmetic products.</em></strong> For cosmetic establishments not required to be licensed by DSHS, and who do not have a current compliant inspection, a nonrefundable fee based on the number of products to be listed on the certificate and $400.00 for inspection conducted by DSHS staff will be required.</li>
	<li><strong><em>Supplemental information review.</em></strong> For a supplemental information review, a separate invoice shall be mailed or sent via facsimile to the applicant. A nonrefundable fee of $72.00 per hour of review time will be charged with a one-half hour minimum. This fee must be paid prior to the certificate being issued. Failure to pay the review fee will result in denial of the certificate.</li>
</ol>
